doc.after: The United Kingdom is buying three KC-135R aircraft for conversion to RC-135W Rivet Joint standard[1] under the Airseeker project.[25] Acquisition of the three aircraft is budgeted at Â£634m (~US$1,000m), with entry into service planned for October 2014.[26] The aircraft will form No. 51 Squadron RAF, based at RAF Waddington along with the RAF's other ISTAR assets. They are expected to remain in British service until 2045.
